The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) based on deep residual network (ResNet) for efficient reconstruction of T2 mapping from single-shot OverLapping-Echo Detachment (OLED) planar imaging. This involves image processing and machine learning, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves simulations and experiments, which could fall under the modeling and simulation (cs.MS) sub-category. The use of ResNet, a popular deep learning architecture, could also place the paper under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
